'''同性戀'''，亦稱為'''同性向'''{{notetag|粤语地区}} 、'''同性愛'''{{notetag|日语地区}} ，是以同样的[[性别|性别]]或[[社会性别|社会性别]]為對象建立起[[浪漫关系|浪漫]]吸引、[[性吸引|性吸引]]或[[性行为|性行为]]的[[親密關係|親密關係]]<!-- 注意:这是来源。此外，“性别”和“社会性别”并不总是同一件事;例如，“性别”可指“生理性别”(男性或女性)，而“社会性别”可指一个人的性别身份是男性或女性;因此，就像性取向、异性恋和双性恋的文章一样，我们把它们都放在了首页。 --><ref name="AmPsycholAssn-definitions">{{cite web|title=Definitions Related to Sexual Orientation and Gender Diversity in APA Documents|publisher=[[美国心理学协会|美国心理学协会]]|date=2015|access-date=February 6, 2020|page=6|url=https://www.apa.org/pi/lgbt/resources/sexuality-definitions.pdf|quote=Sexual orientation refers to the sex of those to whom one is sexually and romantically attracted. [...] [It is] one's enduring sexual attraction to male partners, female partners, or both. Sexual orientation may be heterosexual, samesex (gay or lesbian), or bisexual. [...] A person may be attracted to men, women, both, neither, or to people who are genderqueer, androgynous, or have other gender identities. Individuals may identify as lesbian, gay, heterosexual, bisexual, queer, pansexual, or asexual, among others. [...] Categories of sexual orientation typically have included attraction to members of one's own sex (gay men or lesbians), attraction to members of the other sex (heterosexuals), and attraction to members of both sexes (bisexuals). While these categories continue to be widely used, research has suggested that sexual orientation does not always appear in such definable categories and instead occurs on a continuum [...]. Some people identify as pansexual or queer in terms of their sexual orientation, which means they define their sexual orientation outside of the gender binary of 'male' and 'female' only.|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122054116/https://www.apa.org/pi/lgbt/resources/sexuality-definitions.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，或以此[[性傾向|性傾向]]做為主要自我[[身份认同|認同]]的行為或現象<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=同性戀|encyclopedia=重編國語辭典修訂本|publisher=中華民國教育部|url=http://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/cgi-bin/cbdic/gsweb.cgi?o=dcbdic&searchid=Z00000055682|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214205/http://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/cgi-bin/cbdic/gsweb.cgi?o=dcbdic&searchid=Z00000055682|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同性戀連同[[雙性戀|雙性戀]]和[[異性戀|異性戀]]構成了[[性傾向連續光譜|性傾向連續光譜]]不同程度之別的三區帶<ref name=tongzhi_tw>{{cite book|title=認識同志手冊|year=2011|author=台灣同志諮詢熱線協會|url=http://hotline.org.tw/sites/hotline.org.tw/files/field_upload/ren_shi_tong_zhi_xiu_gai_ban_.pdf|access-date=2015-04-04|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214208/https://hotline.org.tw/sites/hotline.org.tw/files/field_upload/ren_shi_tong_zhi_xiu_gai_ban_.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=APA2008>{{cite book|author=美國心理學學會|title=解答你的問題：深入理解性傾向和同性戀|year=2008|url=http://www.apa.org/topics/lgbt/chinese-orientation.pdf|access-date=2015-04-07|archive-date=2017-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170624000536/http://www.apa.org/topics/lgbt/chinese-orientation.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ritch C. Savin-Williams|title=Sexual Orientation: Categories or Continuum? Commentary on Bailey et al.|journal=Psychological Science in the Public Interest|date=2016|volume=17|issue=2|url=http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/1529100616637618|access-date=2017-05-09|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214221/https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/1529100616637618|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

性傾向是個體對特定[[性別|性別]]之人，感受到的持久性[[情感|情感]]、[[愛慕|愛慕]]或[[性吸引力|性吸引力]]。目前尚無研究能夠明確證實性傾向是由特定、或多種因素所引致<ref name=APA2008/>。但數篇[[性傾向和生物學|生物學理論]]研究論文指出性傾向的形成可能涉及[[基因|基因]]或[[子宮|子宮]]環境等生物性因素<ref>{{cite news|title=The evolutionary puzzle of homosexuality|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-26089486|agency=BBC|accessdate=2016-01-25|archive-date=2015-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151103141404/http://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-26089486|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Bailey">{{cite journal|author1=J. Michael Bailey|author2=Marc Epprecht|author3=Eric Vilain|author4=S. Marc Breedlove|author5=Lisa M. Diamond|author6=Paul L. Vasey|title=Sexual Orientation, Controversy, and Science|journal=Psychological Science in the Public Interest|date=2016|volume=17|issue=2|pages=45-101|url=http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/1529100616637616|quote=No causal theory of sexual orientation has yet gained widespread support. The most scientifically plausible causal hypotheses are difficult to test. However, there is considerably more evidence supporting nonsocial causes of sexual orientation than social causes.|access-date=2017-05-09|archive-date=2021-02-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215080556/https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/1529100616637616|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而由生物因子（[[基因|基因]]、[[激素|激素]]）和非社會性的[[性傾向和環境|環境因子]]共同作用促成<ref name=RCP/><ref>{{cite web|title=Swedish twin study: Q & A with J. Michael Bailey|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2008/07/09/baileyinterview/|access-date=2016-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202132817/http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2008/07/09/baileyinterview/|archive-date=2016-02-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，科學證據不支持能由社會性手段教導或學習性傾向的說法<ref>{{cite news|title=What Scientists Know—And Don't Know—About Sexual Orientation|url=https://www.psychologicalscience.org/news/releases/what-scientists-know-and-dont-know-about-sexual-orientation.html|agency=Association for Psychological Science|date=2016-04-25|quote=Various biological factors--including prenatal hormones and specific genetic profiles--are likely to contribute to sexual orientation, though they are not the sole cause. Scientific evidence suggests that biological and non-social environmental factors jointly influence sexual orientation. -- Scientific findings do not support the notion that sexual orientation can be taught or learned through social means. And there is little evidence to suggest that non-heterosexual orientations become more common with increased social tolerance.|accessdate=2017-05-09|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214242/https://www.psychologicalscience.org/news/releases/what-scientists-know-and-dont-know-about-sexual-orientation.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

科學研究已證實同性戀是人類[[性慾|性慾]]的自然展現型式之一<ref name="APA2008" />，同性戀此性傾向與異性戀、雙性戀相同，其本身不造成任何心理傷害<ref name=APA2008/><ref>{{cite web|author=葉金源|title=對於同性戀者常有的疑問|date=2007-03-27|url=http://psy.med.ncku.edu.tw/files/11-1385-15882.php?Lang=zh-tw|publisher=成功大學醫學院|accessdate=2015-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414180306/http://psy.med.ncku.edu.tw/files/11-1385-15882.php?Lang=zh-tw|archive-date=2015-04-14|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。性傾向可能會在一生中發生某種程度的變化，或未必有固定的[[身份認同|身份認同]]<ref>* {{cite book|author1=Lisa Diamond|title=Concepts of Female Sexual Orientation|date=2013|url=https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=bvy9NaEwPnwC&lpg=PA15&ots=Tc0fcrzScQ&hl=zh-TW&pg=PA7#v=onepage&q&f=false|quote=Historically, researchers have presumed that sexual orientation shows fundamental continuity in its expression over time. Although this is generally true for most individuals, some studies have found that a number of individuals － more often women than men － report notable shifts in same-sex attractions, behaviors, and identities over time.|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214308/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=bvy9NaEwPnwC&lpg=PA15&ots=Tc0fcrzScQ&hl=zh-TW&pg=PA7#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}
* {{cite web|title=Lisa Diamond - Psychology's Feminist Voices|url=http://www.feministvoices.com/lisa-diamond/|quote=Sexual Fluidity attracted substantial media attention. However, the data Diamond collected began to be picked up by anti-gay groups, who espoused that being gay is a choice. Diamond has tried to make her findings clear: she did not find that women "choose" to be gay, or "choose" to become straight, rather, relationships and attractions happen, and there is really no "choice" involved..."This (research) does not mean that sexuality is chosen" - an important point that needs repeating.|access-date=2016-05-11|archive-date=2020-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022093759/http://www.feministvoices.com/lisa-diamond/|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=王晧安|title=性別大補帖：疑性戀就是流性戀|url=https://tw.news.yahoo.com/%E6%80%A7%E5%88%A5%E5%A4%A7%E8%A3%9C%E5%B8%96-%E7%96%91%E6%80%A7%E6%88%80%E5%B0%B1%E6%98%AF%E6%B5%81%E6%80%A7%E6%88%80-161106753.html|agency=台灣立報|date=2013-10-31|accessdate=2016-01-25|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214300/https://tw.news.yahoo.com/%E6%80%A7%E5%88%A5%E5%A4%A7%E8%A3%9C%E5%B8%96-%E7%96%91%E6%80%A7%E6%88%80%E5%B0%B1%E6%98%AF%E6%B5%81%E6%80%A7%E6%88%80-161106753.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=APA Task Force |title=Report of the American Psychological Association Task Force on Appropriate Therapeutic Repsonses to Sexual Orientation |url=https://www.apa.org/pi/lgbt/resources/therapeutic-response.pdf |quote=(a) An enduring change to an individual's sexual orientation as a result of SOCE was unlikely, and some participants were harmed by the interventions; (b) sexual orientation identity—not sexual orientation—appears to change via psychotherapy, support groups, and life events |accessdate=2019-02-24 |archive-date=2013-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603121635/http://www.apa.org/pi/lgbc/publications/therapeutic-response.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>；不過，多數人對自己的性傾向沒有或有極少的選擇意識<ref name=APA2008/><ref name=RCP>{{cite web|author=Royal College of Psychiatrists|title=Royal College of Psychiatrists' statement on sexual orientation|year=2014|url=http://www.rcpsych.ac.uk/pdf/ps02_2014.pdf|accessdate=2015-04-07|archive-date=2017-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809182830/http://www.rcpsych.ac.uk/pdf/PS02_2014.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並且沒有充足可靠的科學證據支持能用心理學手段干預性傾向<ref name=APA2009>{{cite web|author=American Psychological Association|title=Resolution on Appropriate Affirmative Responses to Sexual Orientation Distress and Change Efforts|year=2009|url=http://www.apa.org/about/policy/sexual-orientation.aspx|accessdate=2015-04-07|archive-date=2018-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422190850/http://www.apa.org/about/policy/sexual-orientation.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=APA2000>{{cite web|author=Human Rights Campaign|title=Policy and Position Statements on Conversion Therapy|3=|url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/policy-and-position-statements-on-conversion-therapy|accessdate=2017-05-09|archive-date=2017-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170427021742/http://www.hrc.org/resources/policy-and-position-statements-on-conversion-therapy|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=PAH>{{cite web|author=Pan American Health Organization|title=Cures for an Illness That Does Not Exist|date=2012-05-17|url=http://www.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_docman&task=doc_view&gid=17703|accessdate=2015-04-07|archive-date=2018-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821143749/http://www.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_docman&task=doc_view&gid=17703|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

不少同志處於互相承諾或同居的親密關係，有些也共同育養子女，但直到最近一些國家才展開針對同性親密同居的[[戶口普查|戶口調查]]<ref>{{cite news|language =En|author =Susan Donaldson James|url =http://abcnews.go.com/Health/sex-couples-census-data-trickles-quarter-raising-children/story?id=13850332|title =Census 2010: One-Quarter of Gay Couples Raising Children|publisher =Contra Costa Times|date =2011-06-23|accessdate =2015-04-12|archive-date =2017-06-30|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20170630053712/http://abcnews.go.com/Health/sex-couples-census-data-trickles-quarter-raising-children/story?id=13850332|dead-url =no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Gates, Gary J.; Cooke, Abigail M.|title=United States Census Snapshot: 2010|url=http://williamsinstitute.law.ucla.edu/wp-content/uploads/Census2010Snapshot-US-v2.pdf?r=1|publisher=Williams Institute, UCLA School of Law|year=2011|accessdate=2015-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626224538/http://williamsinstitute.law.ucla.edu/wp-content/uploads/Census2010Snapshot-US-v2.pdf?r=1|archive-date=2015-06-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，同性恋者家戶的生活境況也開始獲得矚目<ref>{{cite web|author=同學陣 hgf|title=Zach Wahls - 我的兩個媽 (My Two Moms)|date=2014-01-27|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6T-khwaef1I|accessdate=2017-05-09|archive-date=2022-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220103064043/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6T-khwaef1I|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language =zh-hans|url =http://www.pflag.org.cn/h-nd-817.html|title =中國同志家庭面臨重重考驗|publisher =鳳凰週刊|date =2015-12-10|accessdate =2015-12-10|archive-date =2021-02-13|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214350/http://www.pflag.org.cn/h-nd-817.html|dead-url =no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=花了十五年，我終於攜愛人同志和兒子回家過年|url=https://theinitium.com/article/20160214-mainland-gayfamily/|agency=端傳媒|date=2016-02-14|accessdate=2016-05-11|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214354/https://theinitium.com/article/20160214-mainland-gayfamily/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=同志家庭與他們的孩子|url=https://www.twreporter.org/topics/same-sex-parents-family|agency=報導者|date=2016-05-06|accessdate=2017-08-26|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214359/https://www.twreporter.org/topics/same-sex-parents-family|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在人類歷史上，同性間的親密關係與[[性行為|性行為]]受過推崇和[[迫害|迫害]]<ref name=Androphile>{{cite web|author=[http://www.gay-art-history.org/ The Androphile Project]|title=同性戀史研究：男性愛的世界史|url=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/93569/49142|year=2009|accessdate=2017-05-09|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100715062632/http://article.yeeyan.org/view/93569/49142|archivedate=2010-07-15}}</ref>，而從十九世紀末開始，爭取同性恋者社群的能見度、同性親密關係社會承認和相關[[各地LGBT權利|法律權利]]的全球性[[同志運動|社會運動]]興起，要求保障同性恋者在婚姻或民事結合、生育撫養、工作就業、從軍入伍、醫療照護上獲得[[平等主義|平等對待]]的權利，並且推動立法或行政措施，制止[[性別歧视|性別歧视]]或對性傾向的[[仇恨言論|仇恨言論]]和[[霸凌|霸凌]]行為<ref name=Montreal>{{cite web|title=Declaration of Montréal|url=http://www.declarationofmontreal.org|year=2006|accessdate=2015-04-08|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214415/http://www.declarationofmontreal.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=yogyakarta>{{cite web|title=日惹原則——關於將國際人權法應用於性傾向和性別認同相關事務的原則|url=http://www.yogyakartaprinciples.org/principles-ch/|year=2006|accessdate=2017-05-09|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214444/http://yogyakartaprinciples.org/principles-ch/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Joint Statement on the Rights of LGBT Persons at the Human Rights Council|url=http://www.state.gov/r/pa/prs/ps/2011/03/158847.htm|year=2011|accessdate=2015-04-21|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421053659/http://www.state.gov/r/pa/prs/ps/2011/03/158847.htm|archivedate=2015-04-21}}</ref>。

