=== 性傾向的形成 ===
{{參見|性傾向和生物學|環境和性取向}}
到目前為止，科學家對於一個人形成異性戀、雙性戀或同性戀的具體原因還沒有達成共識。儘管許多研究考察過可能會影響性傾向的因素，例如[[遺傳|遺傳]]、[[激素|激素]]、成長經驗、社會與文化，但尚無研究能夠明確證實性傾向是由某個特定因素或多種因素所引致的<ref name=APA2008/><ref name="Academy of Pediatrics"/>。

儘管如此，多數科學家認為性傾向的形成，可能是由於生物因子（基因、激素）和孕後環境因子間複雜的[[先天与后天|交互作用]]促成<ref name=RCP/>。他們指出，大多數人的性傾向在童年就已经形成<ref name="Academy of Pediatrics"/><ref name="perrin2002">{{Cite book
 | last = Perrin
 | first = E. C.
 | title = Sexual Orientation in Child and Adolescent Health Care
 | url = https://archive.org/details/sexualorientatio0000perr
 | publisher = Kluwer Academic/Plenum Publishers
 | year = 2002
 | location = New York
 | isbn = 0-306-46761-5
 }}</ref>。現有證據表明，絕大多數擁有女同性戀和男同性戀傾向的成年人，是由異性戀父母養育的。女同性戀和男同性戀父母撫養的孩子絕大多數会成为異性戀<ref name="apahelp">{{cite web|title=Sexual orientation, homosexuality and bisexuality|publisher=[[American_Psychological_Association|American Psychological Association]]|accessdate=2013-08-10|url=http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/sexual-orientation.aspx|archivedate=2013-08-08|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808032050/http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/sexual-orientation.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

最近數十年來，大量證據顯示了生物性因素對於性傾向形成有重大影響<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Qazi Rahman|author2=Glenn D. Wilson|title=Born gay? The psychobiology of human sexual orientation|journal=Personality and Individual Differences|date=2003|volume=34|issue=8|pages=1337–82|doi=10.1016/S0191-8869(02)00140-X|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S019188690200140X|accessdate=2015-08-07|archive-date=2018-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211155152/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S019188690200140X|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=borngay>{{cite news|title='Gay genes': science is on the right track, we're born this way. Let’s deal with it.|url=http://www.theguardian.com/science/blog/2015/jul/24/gay-genes-science-is-on-the-right-track-were-born-this-way-lets-deal-with-it|accessdate=2015-08-07|agency=the Guardian|date=2015-07-24|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214923/https://www.theguardian.com/science/blog/2015/jul/24/gay-genes-science-is-on-the-right-track-were-born-this-way-lets-deal-with-it|dead-url=no}}</ref>，同卵雙胞胎性傾向一致性，以及同家族譜系間特定性傾向的[[聚類分析|集群]]，支持了[[性傾向和生物學|生物學的解釋]]<ref name="Academy of Pediatrics">{{cite journal|author=Frankowski, Barbara L.|coauthors=American Academy of Pediatrics Committee on Adolescence|title=Sexual orientation and adolescents|journal=Pediatrics|date=2004|volume=113|issue=6|pages=1827-32|doi=10.1542/peds.113.6.1827|pmid=15173519|url=http://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/113/6/1827.long|access-date=2015-04-04|archive-date=2013-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130320020943/http://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/113/6/1827.long|dead-url=no}}</ref>。科學家正在尋找與性傾向有關的基因，[[双生子研究|雙生子研究]]为性傾向的遺傳基礎提供實質證據，特別是男同性戀。位於[[X染色體|X染色體]]的Xq28以及[[8號染色體|8號染色體]]的8q12被認為最有可能是包含與男同性戀有關的基因區段<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Ngun | first1 = TC | last2 = Vilain | first2 = E | year = 2014 | title = The biological basis of human sexual orientation: is there a role for epigenetics? | url = | journal = Adv Genet | volume = 86 | issue = | pages = 167–84 | doi = 10.1016/B978-0-12-800222-3.00008-5 | pmid = 25172350 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Dean H. Hame, etc.|title=A Linkage Between DNA Markers on the X Chromosome and Male Sexual Orientation|journal=Science|date=1993|volume=261|issue=5119|pages=321-327|url=http://postcog.ucd.ie/files/2881563.pdf|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140712125537/http://postcog.ucd.ie/files/2881563.pdf|archivedate=2014-07-12|access-date=2015-04-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=A. R. Sanders, etc|title=Genome-wide scan demonstrates significant linkage for male sexual orientation|journal=Psychological Medicine|date=2014|volume=45|issue=7|pages=1379-1388|doi=10.1017/S0033291714002451|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=9625997&fileId=S0033291714002451|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2016-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160422032830/http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=9625997&fileId=S0033291714002451|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|language=en|author1=Andy Coghlan|title=Largest study of gay brothers homes in on 'gay genes'|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn26572-largest-study-of-gay-brothers-homes-in-on-gay-genes.html|accessdate=2015-04-26|agency=NewScientist|date=2014-11-17|archive-date=2015-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150629160712/http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn26572-largest-study-of-gay-brothers-homes-in-on-gay-genes.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。性傾向可能是一種{{tsl|en|Polygene|多基因}}（polygenic）遺傳特徵<ref>{{cite web|author1=王弘毅|title=同性戀是天生後天的老梗有新梗嗎？有！所以是.....|url=http://leplab.blogspot.tw/2014/02/blog-post.html|website=大大養成所|date=2014-02-12|accessdate=2015-04-26|archive-date=2018-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180217204944/http://leplab.blogspot.tw/2014/02/blog-post.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並且基因對於性傾向的形成可能只扮演部分角色<ref>{{cite news|language=en|author1=Sarah Knapton,|title=Being homosexual is only partly due to gay gene, research finds|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/10637532/Being-homosexual-is-only-partly-due-to-gay-gene-research-finds.html|accessdate=2015-04-26|agency=Telegraph|date=2014-02-13|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214914/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/10637532/Being-homosexual-is-only-partly-due-to-gay-gene-research-finds.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有些科學家主張子宮環境影響胎兒的[[表觀遺傳學|表觀遺傳]]（epigenetics）進而調控性傾向的形成<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pansci.tw/archives/32703|title=同性戀可能源於子宮|accessdate=2015-04-26|author=|date=2012-12-14|publisher=|author1=陸子鈞|website=[[PanSci_泛科學|PanSci 泛科學]]|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214917/http://pansci.tw/archives/32703|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，有些研究認為能以此預測性傾向<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Balter|first=Michael|date=2015-10-09|title=BEHAVIORAL GENETICS. Can epigenetics explain homosexuality puzzle?|journal=Science|volume=350|issue=6257|pages=148|doi=10.1126/science.350.6257.148|issn=1095-9203|pmid=26450189}}</ref>，但有專家對其預測的準確性表達懷疑，指其樣本數量過小<ref>{{cite news|title=Epigenetic Test Can Predict Homosexuality, Controversial Study Claims|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/virginiahughes/genetic-on-off-switches-can-predict-homosexuality-controvers|agency=buzzfeed|date=2015-10-08|accessdate=2017-05-27|archive-date=2018-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180501080611/https://www.buzzfeed.com/virginiahughes/genetic-on-off-switches-can-predict-homosexuality-controvers|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

另外一些證據指出激素與性傾向形成有關，一種說法是出生前的[[睪固酮|睪固酮]]濃度影響胎兒腦部結構，在子宮時編譯好特定的性傾向、性別認同以及相關的行為、認知和性格特質<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Garcia-Falgueras A.|author2=Swaab D.F.|title=Sexual Hormones and the Brain: An Essential Alliance for Sexual Identity and Sexual Orientation|journal=Pediatric Neuroendocrinology|date=2010|volume=17|pages=22-35|doi=10.1159/000262525|pmid=19955753|url=http://www.karger.com/Article/Abstract/262525|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225063644/https://www.karger.com/Article/Abstract/262525|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Melissa Hines|journal=Trends in Cognitive Sciences|title=Sex-related variation in human behavior and the brain|date=2010|volume=14|issue=10|pages=448-456|doi=10.1016/j.tics.2010.07.005|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2951011/|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215006/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2951011/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。許多科學家分別考慮了出生順序、慣用手、頭髮漩渦、陰莖長短、身高體重關係，無名指/食指長度比例等因素，來研究{{tsl|en|Prenatal hormones and sexual orientation|激素與性傾向的關聯}}<ref>{{cite web|author1=lescholar|title=同性戀的成因:先天或後天?(暫稿)|url=http://lescholar.pixnet.net/blog/post/159227147|website=同性戀的學術研究|date=2013-09-03|accessdate=2015-04-26|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213214948/https://lescholar.pixnet.net/blog/post/159227147|dead-url=no}}</ref>，Blanchard的研究發現“每多有一个哥哥，該名男子被另外一名男子吸引的可能性就大一些”<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ray Blanchard|title=Birth order and sibling sex ratio in homosexual versus heterosexual males and females|journal=Annual Review of Sex Research|date=1997|volume=8|pages=27-67|pmid=10051890}}</ref>，研究者認為這可能與母體懷多次男胎產生的免疫反應有關<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ray Blanchard|title=Fraternal Birth Order and the Maternal Immune Hypothesis of Male Homosexuality|journal=Hormones and Behavior|date=2001|volume=40|issue=2|pages=105-114|doi=10.1006/hbeh.2001.1681|pmid=11534970|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0018506X01916812|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2019-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528080851/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0018506X01916812|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/uk/2015/11/151108_sibling_clever|title= 研究：出生顺序影响智商、健康和性取向？|access-date= 2015-11-09|archive-date= 2021-02-13|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215008/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/uk/2015/11/151108_sibling_clever|dead-url= no}}</ref>，Blanchard也發現發生該現象的男性多數都是右撇子<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ray Blanchard|title=Review and theory of handedness, birth order, and homosexuality in men|date=2008|volume=13|issue=1|pages=51-70|doi=10.1080/13576500701710432|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/13576500701710432#.VTyX65PCnX8|journal=|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2019-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190518101236/https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/13576500701710432#.VTyX65PCnX8|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

其他的研究指出[[生理學|生理學]]和性傾向的相關性。在神經內分泌學與神經解剖學方面，{{link-en|西蒙·列维|Simon LeVay}}的研究報告男女同性戀與男女異性戀間有若干腦神經核型態（[[下視丘|INAH]]3）差異存在<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Simon LeVay|title=A difference in hypothalamic structure between heterosexual and homosexual men|journal=Science|date=1991|volume=30|issue=5023|pages=1034-1037|doi=10.1126/science.1887219|url=http://www.sciencemag.org/content/253/5023/1034|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2016-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160104183753/http://www.sciencemag.org/content/253/5023/1034|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但該研究遭到樣本量不足以及選擇偏誤的批評，尚未得到進一步的廣泛驗證<ref>{{cite journal|author1=William Byne, etc.|title=The Interstitial Nuclei of the Human Anterior Hypothalamus: An Investigation of Variation with Sex, Sexual Orientation, and HIV Status|journal=Hormones and Behavior|date=2001|volume=40|issue=2|pages=86-92|doi=10.1006/hbeh.2001.1680|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0018506X01916800|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2020-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710025529/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0018506X01916800|dead-url=no}}</ref>。另一份研究指出性[[信息素|信息素]]反應的差異，男性同性戀者和女性異性戀者的腦部會對[[雄二烯酮|雄二烯酮]]有性反應，女性同性戀者和男性異性戀者的腦部則對[[雌四烯醇|雌四烯醇]]有性反應<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ivanka Savic|author2=Per Lindström|author3=Hans Berglund|title=Brain response to putative pheromones in homosexual men|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|date=2005|volume=102|issue=20|pages=7356–7361|doi=10.1073/pnas.0407998102|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1129091/|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225225517/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1129091/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ivanka Savic|author2=Per Lindström|author3=Hans Berglund|title=Brain response to putative pheromones in lesbian women|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|date=2006|volume=103|issue=21|pages=8269–8274.|doi=10.1073/pnas.0600331103|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1570103/|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-date=2022-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220103070325/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1570103/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 性傾向身分 ===
[[File:Gay_pride_090_-_Marche_des_fiertés_Toulouse_2011.jpg|150px]]
{{參見|性傾向身分}}
就科學研究和專業人員的瞭解，性傾向通常在[[童年|童年]]中期至[[青春期|青春期]]初期感受到。這些情感、愛情及性吸引，可能在毫無性經驗的情況下產生。不同的人在性傾向上的體驗也會很不同，有人很早就確定了自己的性傾向，但也有些人在與同性或異性伴侶發生過性行為之後，才真的明確了自己的性傾向<ref name=APA2008/>。根據[[克萊因性傾向方格|克萊因性傾向方格]]，探索自我性傾向，可由情-{欲}-吸引、性行為、性幻想、情感偏好、社交偏好、生活形態偏好、自我認同等向度著手。以上這些向度並非都要符合，不同人可能有不同的方式界定自己的性傾向，但只有本人自己透過自己對性吸引的感覺和感情慾望，才能做出判斷<ref name=tongzhi(edu)_tw />。

心理學及性別研究對於性特質（sexuality）之多面向與多樣性的理解，已為當代精神醫學採納，性傾向是內在先天的特質，性行為和性身份（sexual identity）較偏向是在發展過程中自由意志的選擇<ref name=gaypsy>{{cite journal|author1=賴孟泉|author2=紀品志|title=不再是醫師： 簡述當代精神醫學對性傾向的觀點|journal=輔導季刊|date=2009|volume=45|issue=4|pages=58-70|url=http://web.ntnu.edu.tw/~chunghan/pdf/001.pdf|author=|access-date=2015-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117025318/http://web.ntnu.edu.tw/~chunghan/pdf/001.pdf|archive-date=2015-11-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。因此，性行為與性傾向不必然有關，與同性發生過性行為，情感偏好不一定是同性；與異性發生性行為，性幻想對象也不一定是異性<ref>{{cite news|language=zh-hk|title=性取向與性行為概念不同|url=http://www.mingpaocanada.com/TOR/htm/News/20141115/wha.htm|accessdate=2015-04-26|agency=明報|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215107/http://www.mingpaocanada.com/TOR/htm/News/20141115/wha.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。例如，监狱或其它性别隔离环境中，可能致使[[异性恋|异性恋]]男性和同性發生[[境遇性性行为|境遇性性行为]]，虽然他们回到外面的环境仍偏好异性<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|author=Tina Gianoulis|title=Situational Homosexuality|publisher=glbtq, inc.|url=http://www.glbtqarchive.com/ssh/situational_homosexuality_S.pdf|access-date=2016-10-10|archive-date=2020-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926094816/http://www.glbtqarchive.com/ssh/situational_homosexuality_S.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有些男性[[性工作者|性工作者]]比如[[妓男|妓男]]或者[[男男同性色情片演員|男男色情演员]]亦可能是從事[[男男性交易|男男性交易]]來營生的异性恋男性<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Jeffrey Escoffier|title=Gay-for-Pay: Straight Men and the Making of Gay Pornography|journal=Qualitative Sociology|date=2003|volume=26|url=http://pzacad.pitzer.edu/~mma/teaching/ms110/reading/gayforpay.pdf|access-date=2016-10-10|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122054955/http://pzacad.pitzer.edu/~mma/teaching/ms110/reading/gayforpay.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。偏見和歧視令許多人難以接受自己的性傾向，所以認同自己的性傾向身份可能是一個緩慢的過程<ref name=APA2008/>。

主張[[社會建構主義|社會建構論]]或[[酷兒理論|酷兒理論]]的學者，批判或不理會性傾向的生物性成因，而是研究同性戀的社會身份如何成為[[社会控制|社會控制]]的機制，或者壓制了多重身份展現的可能性<ref>{{cite journal|author1=郭曉飛|title=本質的還是建構的?論性傾向平等保護中的「不可改變」進路|journal=法学家|date=2009|volume=2009|issue=1|pages=123-139|url=http://sex.ncu.edu.tw/publication/2011/changing_sexual_landscape/pdf/03.pdf|access-date=2015-08-07|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122055005/http://sex.ncu.edu.tw/publication/2011/changing_sexual_landscape/pdf/03.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。建構論主張，由於「同性戀」與「異性戀」的分類存在，人們不由自主地將自己「對號入座」；如果沒有這番[[標籤效應|標籤]]，只將性行為當作一種性表達就不會有「正常」與否的分野。該觀點的始祖法國哲學家[[米歇爾·傅柯|米歇爾·傅柯]]，指出「同性戀」和「同性戀者」等名稱的產生，使一群「與同性發生性關係的人」正式被視為一個具有某些特徵的社群。利用這些特徵，人們可以清楚地將同性戀者與其他人分辨開，必要時可以將他們隔離起來。傅柯認為同性戀身份的社會建構，造成了對同性戀的壓制，但對它的[[解构|解构]]可以成為前進的武器和工具<ref name=gay_Sc2>{{cite web|author1=二言|title=同性戀：本質還是建構？|url=http://www.sex-study.org/news.php?isweb=2&sort=64&id=636|website=中國人民大學性社會學研究所|accessdate=2015-08-07|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304124350/http://www.sex-study.org/news.php?isweb=2&sort=64&id=636|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。對此，Joshua Gamsom提出了批評。他說：「解構身分類別，模糊群體邊界。」而當同性戀者群體邊界變得模糊時，同性戀者這一族群就沒有固定、堅實的身分和範圍。「沒有一個堅實的群體身分，就無法提出任何要求……它就難以完成任何集體行動」<ref>{{cite journal|author1=楊惠南|title=我所知道的台灣同性戀佛教徒|journal=弘誓雙月刊|volume=83|url=http://hongshi.org.tw/writings.aspx?code=E0555DAE96B329D8F478C9BD4BF3A3B2|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215104/http://hongshi.org.tw/writings.aspx?code=E0555DAE96B329D8F478C9BD4BF3A3B2|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 出櫃與人口數 ===
[[出櫃|出櫃]]源自於英文「Coming out (of the closet)」，指承認、接受和欣賞自身的[[性傾向|性傾向]]或[[性別認同|性別認同]]，並將之與他人分享的歷程。與之相對的，隱瞞而不願表達，稱之為「躲在衣櫃」或未出櫃（Closeted）<ref>{{cite web|author1=Human Rights Campaign Foundation|title=Glossary of Terms|url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/glossary-of-terms|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2015-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117012459/http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/glossary-of-terms|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一般而言，出櫃可分為三個階段：第一階段是認識自我，願意對自己坦承，第二階段是向他人出櫃，將同志身份告知親友同事，第三階段是公開生活，將同志身份自由公開地融入生活之中。<ref>{{cite web|author1=Human Rights Campaign Foundation|title=Resource Guide to Coming Out|url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/resource-guide-to-coming-out|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2015-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023011947/http://www.hrc.org/resources/entry/resource-guide-to-coming-out|dead-url=no}}</ref>。近年來，美國[[人口普查|人口普查]]呈現同性伴侶增多的現象，似乎反映了同性戀者被社會接納認可程度的巨大變化，越來越多同性戀者願意公開性傾向或公開與同性伴侶的關係<ref>{{cite web|title=美國人口普查數據顯示同性戀伴侶家庭分布和增長狀況|url=http://www.2girl.net/article-7660-1.html|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215121/https://www.2girl.net/article-7660-1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=In US, More Adults Identifying as LGBT|url=http://www.gallup.com/poll/201731/lgbt-identification-rises.aspx?src=www.danlan.org|access-date=2017-01-14|archive-date=2017-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116154137/http://www.gallup.com/poll/201731/lgbt-identification-rises.aspx?src=www.danlan.org|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

LGBT人口最早的大規模研究，首推[[阿爾弗雷德·金賽|阿爾弗雷德·金賽]]。他的[[金賽報告|性學報告]]採用[[金賽量表|金賽量表]]來測量性傾向的傾向程度<ref>{{cite web|author1=Kinsey Institute|title=Kinsey's Heterosexual-Homosexual Rating Scale|url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/research/ak-hhscale.html|accessdate=2015-04-26|archive-date=2015-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151204161037/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/research/ak-hhscale.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，其研究發現[[美國|美國]]近46%的男性在成人生活中，對男女都有性反應，帶有至少某種程度的雙性戀傾向，37%的男性曾發生同性性接觸並達到快感，他們在报告中指出：「由於成年人后的一生中只有50%的人是绝对異性性行为者，只有4%是绝对同性性行为者，因此人口中就有46%（近一半）的人既有異性性行为，又有同性性行为<ref>{{cite book|title=金赛性学报告|author=阿尔弗雷德·C·金赛 |publisher=海南出版社 三环出版社|others=潘绥铭译|date=2007-05|page=191|isbn=9787807001263}}</ref>。」。不過而其統計結果由於是採用方便抽樣，而非機率抽樣，所以遭到像[[约翰·图基|約翰·圖基]]般的統計學家的批評<ref>{{Cite journal
|author=David Leonhardt
|title=John Tukey, 85, Statistician; Coined the Word 'Software'
|journal=The New York Times
|date=28 July 2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|title=Biography 15.1, ''John W. Tukey'' (1915–2000)
|url=http://www.swlearning.com/quant/kohler/stat/biographical_sketches/bio15.1.html
|accessdate=19 May 2009
|archive-date=2017-11-05
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171105192244/http://www.swlearning.com/quant/kohler/stat/biographical_sketches/bio15.1.html
|dead-url=no
}} John Tukey criticizes sample procedure</ref>。在20世紀70年代時，第二任金賽研究所的主任{{link-en|保羅·格布哈特|Paul Gebhard}}移除一些被指偏頗的嫌疑數據後重新計算<ref name=gebhardrelia>{{cite web|url=http://www.pbs.org/fmc/interviews/gebhard.htm|title=NEW RIVER MEDIA INTERVIEW WITH: PAUL GEBHARD  Colleague of Alfred Kinsey 1946–1956  Former Director of the Kinsey Institute|author=New River Media|publisher=PBS.org|accessdate=2014-10-27|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215204/http://www.pbs.org/fmc/interviews/gebhard.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，試圖證明金賽的研究是真实的，並發現原來和更新的數字之間只有細微的差別<ref>Gathorne-Hardy, Jonathan (2005). ''Kinsey: A Biography'', p 285. London: Pimlico</ref>。神經科學家{{link-en|西蒙·萊維|Simon LeVay}}引用以上結果去解釋人口統計需要謹慎的原因——儘管採用了合理的科學方法，但所採用的處理標準仍會大大影響最終結果<ref name="levay">[[Simon_LeVay|LeVay, Simon]] (1996). ''[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/longterm/books/chap1/queerscience.htm Queer Science: The Use and Abuse of Research into Homosexuality] {{Wayback|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/longterm/books/chap1/queerscience.htm |date=20171213181804 }}.'' Cambridge: The MIT Press {{ISBN|0-262-12199-9}}</ref>。一些同性戀權益組織認為，按照世界公認數據，同性戀人口亦占人口總數的4%~6%的比例<ref name=gay_china>{{cite news|title=「不再恐同日」，同性戀權利在抗爭|url=http://www.dw.com/zh/%E4%B8%8D%E5%86%8D%E6%81%90%E5%90%8C%E6%97%A5%E5%90%8C%E6%80%A7%E6%81%8B%E6%9D%83%E5%88%A9%E5%9C%A8%E6%8A%97%E4%BA%89/a-16821392|agency=德國之聲|date=2013-05-17|accessdate=2015-11-12|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215238/https://www.dw.com/zh/%E4%B8%8D%E5%86%8D%E6%81%90%E5%90%8C%E6%97%A5%E5%90%8C%E6%80%A7%E6%81%8B%E6%9D%83%E5%88%A9%E5%9C%A8%E6%8A%97%E4%BA%89/a-16821392|dead-url=no}}</ref>，美國同志平權組織{{tsl|en|National LGBTQ Task Force|National LGBTQ Task Force}}則估算[[LGBT|LGBT]]人口為5–10%<ref>{{cite web|author1=Jaime Grant|title=How Big is the LGBT Community?  Why Can’t I Find This Number?|url=http://www.thetaskforce.org/static_html/downloads/release_materials/tf_lgbt_community.pdf|access-date=2015-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305180019/http://www.thetaskforce.org/static_html/downloads/release_materials/tf_lgbt_community.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。 

關於同性戀或雙性戀群體所占的人口比例，受限於同性戀的[[操作定义|操作定义]]和不願揭露其同志身份的緣故，不同的統計調查會有不同的結果<ref name="lgbt_sample">{{cite journal|title=Sampling Lesbian, Gay, and Bisexual Populations|author=Meyer, Ilan H.|url=http://www.columbia.edu/~im15/papers/sampling.pdf|journal=Journal of Counseling Psychology|issue=1|doi=10.1037/a0014587|year=2009|volume=56|pages=23-31|coauthors=Wilson, Patrick A.|access-date=2015-04-14|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122055106/http://www.columbia.edu/~im15/papers/sampling.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=lgbt_p2>{{cite web|title=LGB人口|url=http://lescholar.pixnet.net/blog/post/76205436|website=同性戀的學術研究|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215240/https://lescholar.pixnet.net/blog/post/76205436|dead-url=no}}</ref>。研究者區別了三種不同的定義概念，性行为、性吸引力和性身份認同，這三者并不一定是一致的<ref>同性戀的操作定義可分為性行为、性吸引力和性身份認同，然而這三者仍然很難完全一致地測量到同性戀所佔的人口比例。例如，性行為雖然有客觀的測量和準則，但是「過去一年內」、「過去五年內」、「18歲以後」或「曾經有過」同性性行為的比例會有所不同，而且會排除掉是同性戀但尚未有過性行為的人。而一個人對自我的性身份認同很可能大相逕庭，不同的世代、族群、地區、教育程度會影響自我是否接受同性戀或同志的身份標籤。性吸引力的測量則又取決於多大程度的好感，算是有性吸引力，定義為「雙性都有」、「僅限於同性」測量到的比例又會有所差異。</ref>，並且會影響調查出來的人口比例。根據一份1995年的研究，在美國、英國和法國，完全只從事同性性行為的人只佔約1%，但若定義放寬到「對同性有過性行為或者性吸引力的人（不排除對異性也有的情況）」，則比例會擴增至近20%左右<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ritch C. Savin-Williams|title=How Many Gays Are There? It Depends|journal=Contemporary Perspectives on Lesbian, Gay, and Bisexual Identities|date=2009|pages=5-41|doi=10.1007/978-0-387-09556-1_2|url=http://www.springer.com/cda/content/document/cda_downloaddocument/9780387095554-c2.pdf?SGWID=0-0-45-670021-p173824328|access-date=2015-11-12|archive-date=2021-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210919000428/https://www.springer.com/cda/content/document/cda_downloaddocument/9780387095554-c2.pdf?SGWID=0-0-45-670021-p173824328|dead-url=no}} These definitional dilemmas are not restricted to one age group or one culture. In  the United  States, the United Kingdom, and France, exclusive same-sex behavior rarely characterized more than 1% of the adult population. If the definition was broadened to include individuals who had both same- and opposite-sex behavior, who had some degree of same-sex attraction, or at least one of the two, then the proportion of gays expanded considerably– nearly one-fifth of the population of men and women (p. 18). 該數據引自 Sell, R. L., Wells, J. A., & Wypij, D. (1995). The prevalence of homosexual behavior and attraction in the United States, the United Kingdom and France: Results of national population-
based samples. Archives of Sexual Behavior, 24, 235–248.</ref>。相較於性吸引力或性行為，性身份認同測量到的人群比較少。1994年一份全美國的性行為研究指出，美國僅有2.41％的男性與1.32％的女性同時符合慾望、行為與認同三項同性戀測量指標<ref name = Laumann1994>Laumann, E. O., Gagnon, J. H., Michael, R. T., & Michaels, S. (1994). ''The social organization of sexuality: Sexual practices in the United States.'' Chicago: University of Chicago Press.</ref>。在一份2006年的研究，20%的人報告對同性有同性戀情感，然而只有2–3%認同自己是同性戀者<ref>{{cite journal|author1=McConaghy, N et al.|title=Fraternal Birth Order and Ratio of Heterosexual/Homosexual Feelings in Women and Men|journal=Journal of Homosexuality|date=2006|volume=51|issue=4|pages=161-174|doi=10.1300/J082v51n04_09|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1300/J082v51n04_09#.VkNSgb_CmNo|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224182754/https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1300/J082v51n04_09#.VkNSgb_CmNo|dead-url=no}}</ref>。根據[[UCLA|UCLA]]{{tsl|en|Williams Institute|威廉姆斯研究所}}2011年的資料，美國3.5%人口自我認同為同性戀者或雙性戀者，8.2%表示有過同性性接觸，11%承認某種程度對同性感受到性吸引力<ref name=lgb_p3>{{cite web|author1=Gary J. Gates|title=How Many People are Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender?|url=http://williamsinstitute.law.ucla.edu/research/census-lgbt-demographics-studies/how-many-people-are-lesbian-gay-bisexual-and-transgender/|website=The Williams Institute|access-date=2015-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130830202655/http://williamsinstitute.law.ucla.edu/research/census-lgbt-demographics-studies/how-many-people-are-lesbian-gay-bisexual-and-transgender/|archive-date=2013-08-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

目前幾乎沒有針對同性戀者展開的[[人口普查|人口普查]]數據，只有研究報告或抽樣調查供作參考<ref name=lgb_4>{{cite news|title=How to count how many people are gay|url=http://www.economist.com/blogs/economist-explains/2015/05/economist-explains-3|agency=The Economist|date=2013-05-05|accessdate=2015-11-12|archive-date=2019-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191014133809/https://www.economist.com/blogs/economist-explains/2015/05/economist-explains-3|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這些數據有可能因為調查方法和[[LGBT|LGBT]]不願揭露身份的緣故而低估實際人口數，當社會愈來愈趨向平等，這些數據的真實性就有可能提高<ref name=lgbr_PP>{{cite web|title=LGBT counselors question statistics on sexual orientation|url=http://ct.counseling.org/2014/08/lgbt-counselors-question-statistics-on-sexual-orientation/|access-date=2016-01-12|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215234/https://ct.counseling.org/2014/08/lgbt-counselors-question-statistics-on-sexual-orientation/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。各種「男同性戀、女同性戀或雙性戀」人口數據，如下：
* 1991年，{{tsl|en|NORC at the University of Chicago|芝加哥大學國家民意調查中心}}執行的{{tsl|en|General Social Survey|一般社會調查}}，報告過去一年內，3.2%男性有過男性性伴侶，過去五年內，4.1%男性有過男性性伴侶，自18歲起，5.1%的男性有過男性性伴侶。三者含括起來，共有3.9%為同性或雙性戀者<ref>[http://www3.norc.org/NR/rdonlyres/2663F09F-2E74-436E-AC81-6FFBF288E183/0/AmericanSexualBehavior2006.pdf “American Sexual Behavior: Trends, Socio-Demographic Differences and Risk-Behavior”] {{Wayback|url=http://www3.norc.org/NR/rdonlyres/2663F09F-2E74-436E-AC81-6FFBF288E183/0/AmericanSexualBehavior2006.pdf |date=20120516181404 }}, Tom W. Smith, National Opinion Research Center, 1998年12月</ref>。
* 1992年，由Laumann主持的National Health and Social Life Survey利用隨機樣本抽出美國三千多人調查，報告過去一年內，2.7%男性有過男性性伴侶，1.3%女性有過女性性伴侶，自18歲起，4.9%男性有過男性性伴侶，4.1%女性有過女性性伴侶。自我認同為同性戀（2%）或雙性戀（0.8%）男性佔2.8%，自我認同為同性戀（0.9%）或雙性戀（0.5%）女性佔1.4%。該研究還發現認同自身為同性戀或雙性戀的男女，通常有良好的教育背景，屬於中等或高等社會階層，集中在城市地區，例如美國最大12個城市，9%男性和3%女性受訪者自我認同為同性戀或雙性戀<ref name=lgbt_p2/><ref>[http://popcenter.uchicago.edu/data/nhsls.shtml National Health and Social Life Survey] {{Wayback|url=http://popcenter.uchicago.edu/data/nhsls.shtml |date=20180116035539 }}，Population Research Center，芝加哥大学</ref>。
* 1995年，Sell等人以美國、英國、法國以16-50歲的人做為母體，發現過去五年內，美國6.2%男性/3.6%女性、英國4.5%男性/2.1%女性、法國10.7%男性/3.3%女性，跟同性發生過性行為。自15歲起，有同性性行為或同性性吸引的比例，美國20.8%男性/17.8%女性、英國16.3%男性/18.6%女性、法國18.5%男性/18.5%女性<ref name=lgbt_p2/>。
* 1998年，Christopher Bagley和Pierre Tremblay，對加拿大[[卡加利|卡加利]]市18-27歲男性進行分層抽樣調查，研究表示15.3%的男性“報告說有一定程度的同性戀”，其中14%和同性有過性接觸，11.1%自我認同為同性戀（佔5.9%）或雙性戀（佔6.1%），9.2%在過去半年內有過一段同性交往關係（4.3%只限同性，4.9%不限同性）<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Bagley, C.|author2=Tremblay, P.|title=On the prevalence of homosexuality and bisexuality, in a random community survey of 750 men aged 18 to 27|journal=Journal of Homosexuality|date=1998|volume=36|issue=2|pages=1-18|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9736328|access-date=2015-11-12|archive-date=2020-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200513075320/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9736328|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
* 2006-2008年，[[美國疾病控制與預防中心|美國疾病控制與預防中心]]執行National Survey of Family Growth，依機率抽樣13495個15-44歲的樣本，報告5.2%的男性，12.5%的女性曾有過同性性行為。自我認同為同性戀（1.8%）或雙性戀（2.3%）的男性佔4.1%，自我認同為同性戀（1.3%）或雙性戀（2.8%）的女性佔4.1%<ref name=lgbt_p2/>。
