T372|quote=In a culture of homophobia (an irrational fear of gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender [GLBT] people), GLBT people often face a heightened risk of violence specific to their sexual identities.|archive-date=2015-05-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150515225222/https://books.google.com/books?id=lP1yAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT372|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Schuiling">{{cite book|authors=Kerri Durnell Schuiling, Frances E. Likis|title=Women's Gynecologic Health|isbn=0763756377|publisher=[[Jones_&_Bartlett_Publishers|Jones & Bartlett Publishers]]|year=2011|pages=187–188|accessdate=2014-12-27|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pj_ourS3PBMC&pg=PA186|quote=Homophobia is an individual's irrational fear or hate of homosexual people. This may include bisexual or transgender persons, but sometimes the more distinct terms of biphobia or transphobia, respectively, are used.|archive-date=2015-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150514170148/https://books.google.com/books?id=pj_ourS3PBMC&pg=PA186|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Homophobia bundle">*{{cite web|url=http://www.webster.com/dictionary/homophobia|title=webster.com|accessdate=2008-01-29|year=2008|archive-date=2012-12-05|archive-url=https://archive.today/20121205072838/http://www.webster.com/dictionary/homophobia|dead-url=yes}}
